Queens Park Rangers striker Loic Remy has joined up with his team-mates following the collapse of his proposed move to Liverpool.

France international Remy looked set to complete a permanent move away from Loftus Road before he failed a medical at Liverpool.

Remy, who impressed while on loan at Newcastle last season by scoring 14 league goals, even travelled to America to finalise his move to Brendan Rodgers' side.

