Surprise arrival: Loic Remy is in Ireland to take part in QPR's pre-season training camp in Ireland

On his travels: Remy has flown back from the US to link up with his QPR team-mates ahead of the new season

Back in west London: Remy will now stay at QPR if he doesn't receive any other offers to leave the club

However the 27-year-old has now returned to QPR and is in contention to take part in his side's pre-season friendly match against Athlone Town on Tuesday evening.

Harry Redknapp said he was willing to accept Remy back into his squad and questioned Liverpool's decision to pull the plug on the £8.5million move.

The former Portsmouth boss will be hoping Remy can score the goals to help QPR consolidate their place in the Premier League this season.

